initial statement:
 1103
Your Honor,

I stand before you today to plead guilty for the offense of stealing 1000 pounds from the cash register at the café where I used to work. I am deeply remorseful for my actions and take full responsibility for the harm I have caused.

I would like to express my sincere apologies to my former boss for betraying her trust. I acknowledge that my actions were a breach of the faith she had placed in me, and I am truly sorry for abusing that trust.

I want to assure the court that my intention was never to cause significant harm or financial loss to the café. I took only small amounts, ranging from 10 to 20 pounds, over a period of time. I believed that my actions would go unnoticed, and I deeply regret that I was mistaken in thinking so.

It is important to note that I am 25 years old, and this incident marks the first and only offense on my record. I have led a law-abiding life up until now, and I deeply regret this lapse in judgment. My lack of criminal history is a testament to my character and my commitment to being a responsible member of society.

Although I understand that restitution cannot fully rectify the damage caused, I would like to emphasize my sincere intention to repay my former boss for the funds that I stole. I am aware that this may not be possible immediately, given my current financial situation after losing my job. However, I am committed to finding a way to make amends and fulfill my obligation.

In seeking leniency from the court, I would like to highlight that I have already suffered significant personal consequences as a result of my actions. Losing my job has been a wake-up call, and I am dedicated to learning from this experience and ensuring that I never repeat such behavior.

Furthermore, I have taken several steps to address and rectify my behavior. I have sought counseling to better understand the reasons behind my actions and to develop healthier coping mechanisms. I am committed to my own personal growth and will continue to take proactive measures to ensure that I do not engage in any criminal activity in the future.

Your Honor, I humbly request the court's leniency, taking into consideration my plea of guilt, my lack of prior criminal record, and my commitment to making amends for my actions. I assure the court and my former boss that I am genuinely remorseful for the harm I have caused and am dedicated to becoming a responsible and law-abiding member of society.

Thank you for considering my plea.

Sincerely,
Olivia Jones
