Over a period of time, I regrettably took small amounts ranging from 10 to 20 pounds from the cash register on a weekly basis, foolishly thinking that my actions would go unnoticed. I now fully comprehend the gravity of my mistake and the significant impact it has had on those involved.

While it pains me to admit that I am currently unable to repay the full amount due to my financial situation after losing my job, I genuinely intend to rectify my wrongdoing and eventually reimburse my former boss for the funds I wrongfully took. I am committed to exploring every possible avenue to make amends and fulfill my obligations.

Your Honor, I humbly implore the court's leniency, taking into consideration my sincere admission of guilt and the fact that I have no prior criminal record. I have always endeavored to lead an honest and law-abiding life, and this offense represents a regrettable lapse of judgment on my part.

